                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/80: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berne</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-01-28T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 28, 1926—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received January 23—10:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. Department’s No. 10, January 22, 5 p.m. Drummond tells me that so far no
                    Government has requested postponement although there are indications that both
                    France and Italy would welcome such action. He feels that the chances are
                    slightly against postponement, and has promised to keep me fully and promptly
                    informed of any developments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gibson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
